1
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:43,800
Kluay.

2
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:46,600
You can come out now.

3
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:50,040
Other people need to use the restroom too.

4
00:02:52,160 --> 00:02:55,200
I… I told you, just a minute.

5
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:57,480
Don't tell me you're shy.

6
00:02:58,400 --> 00:03:00,680
We've acted like a couple so many times.

7
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:04,800
Don't tell me you're shy now.

8
00:03:04,880 --> 00:03:07,160
Or are you secretly crying because

9
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:11,200
I made that Detwadee guy feel hurt?

10
00:03:11,880 --> 00:03:12,720
Ugh.

11
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:15,840
His name is Detbodin. Detbodin.

12
00:03:15,920 --> 00:03:17,120
What's Detwadee?

13
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:19,720
You really like bullying people,
even their names.

14
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:23,480
I'm not bullying.
Whatever his name is, it doesn't matter.

15
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:24,760
You can come out now.

16
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:28,600
I promise I won't tell anyone.

17
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:32,640
Even Mr. Arnon won't know

18
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:35,120
that you kissed me
to show off in front of Det.

19
00:03:49,480 --> 00:03:50,680
Mr. Warat.

20
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:56,320
If you tell anyone about this,
you'll be in trouble.

21
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:59,000
Okay. I promise I won't tell.

22
00:03:59,600 --> 00:04:03,360
I just… I don't want anyone
to misunderstand me.

23
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:07,280
By now, Det must have
imagined all sorts of things.

24
00:04:07,880 --> 00:04:10,440
Listen. If you keep thinking like this,

25
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:13,080
you're the one who's going to go crazy.

26
00:04:13,160 --> 00:04:15,560
You can't care about everyone
in this world. Believe me.

27
00:04:17,880 --> 00:04:19,279
I'm not arguing with you anymore.

28
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:23,680
But if you tease me about this again,
I'll disappear from your life.

29
00:04:28,640 --> 00:04:31,400
Even if the CCTV
couldn't capture the thief's face,

30
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:34,920
I'm sure I could identify him.

31
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:39,640
If that's the case,
the suspect sketch could help, right?

32
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:42,960
But I need to be discharged
from the hospital first.

33
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:47,880
I think your health
should be our priority.

34
00:04:47,960 --> 00:04:50,840
As for the investigation,
let the police handle it.

35
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:54,680
They're already sending patrol officers
to Baan Saeng every night.

36
00:04:54,760 --> 00:04:58,680
When I get discharged,
I plan to stay with Mama Toi and Som.

37
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:01,480
I was going to stay overnight at home too.

38
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:03,240
But Mom and Som said

39
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:07,200
I should stay at Vanich house
and take care of you instead.

40
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:08,840
I don't really understand why.

41
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:12,280
Your mom and sister are right.

42
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:14,920
Let your sister take care of Baan Saeng
with your mom.

43
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:17,840
You focus on Mr. Arnon and the case.

44
00:05:17,920 --> 00:05:20,160
Mr. Warat is right.

45
00:05:27,440 --> 00:05:29,040
Oh.

46
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:32,440
The food arrived just in time.
It's from your grandmother.

47
00:05:33,280 --> 00:05:34,280
Wow.

48
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:37,160
Grandma really went all out.

49
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:40,080
Are you hungry? Want to eat now?

50
00:05:40,160 --> 00:05:41,360
Or are you still shy?

51
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:44,720
I'm not eating.

52
00:05:48,080 --> 00:05:49,800
- There's duck too.
- I'm not eating.

53
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:54,320
Anong.

54
00:05:55,160 --> 00:05:57,120
Who did this to you? Tell me.

55
00:05:58,640 --> 00:05:59,720
They…

56
00:06:02,080 --> 00:06:04,680
They came to collect the debt.

57
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:21,480
Kaew. Kaew!

58
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:25,040
Kaew!

59
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:31,840
You're not Kaew.

60
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:34,640
Kaew sent me to settle things with you.

61
00:06:34,720 --> 00:06:36,400
He said you refused to pay me.

62
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:37,920
Serves you right.

63
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:43,480
Who told you to stab him?
And you still dare show your face to me?

64
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:45,080
Go hide somewhere.

65
00:06:45,160 --> 00:06:47,520
Don't let this get traced back to me.

66
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:49,880
Otherwise, I won't keep you around.

67
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:51,680
What about my money?

68
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:55,320
Why should I give it to you? Damn, Kaew.

69
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:59,000
If I had known he wasn't coming,

70
00:06:59,080 --> 00:07:00,720
I wouldn't have come all the way here.

71
00:07:01,320 --> 00:07:03,520
Kaew said
you were looking for a debt collector.

72
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:06,400
That's me. What kind do you need?

73
00:07:18,520 --> 00:07:19,840
What are you doing?

74
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:23,400
Does it hurt?

75
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:30,200
I'm asking you, does it hurt?

76
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:32,240
Does it hurt?!

77
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:34,160
Does it hurt?! Does it?

78
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:35,680
So what if it hurts?

79
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:36,840
- What are you going to do?
- Ouch.

80
00:07:36,920 --> 00:07:38,480
- What are you going to do to me?
- Ow, hey!

81
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:51,160
Is that all you've got?

82
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:54,600
Slap me again.

83
00:07:56,520 --> 00:07:58,600
I told you to slap me again.

84
00:07:59,360 --> 00:08:00,320
- Slap me!
- Hey!

85
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:03,160
Come on. More.

86
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:04,240
Ugh!

87
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:07,080
More!

88
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:09,600
- Uh!
- More.

89
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:13,840
<i>I begged for my life, bowed and pleaded.</i>

90
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:17,440
<i>But they wouldn't listen.</i>

91
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:27,480
Are you sure
you don't want to report this?

92
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:32,559
I think they'd only get angrier.

93
00:08:32,640 --> 00:08:36,080
And besides, they might come here
to collect the debt anytime.

94
00:08:36,159 --> 00:08:38,640
I don't want you to get into trouble.

95
00:08:39,280 --> 00:08:40,760
Don't worry.

96
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:42,320
I'll handle it myself.

97
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:45,120
Give me the account number.
I'll transfer the money to them.

98
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:47,640
I still have some money left.

99
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:49,680
I'll take responsibility.

100
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:52,040
Whether it's my money or yours,

101
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:54,800
I'll handle it.

102
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:58,800
Hurry and transfer it back to them.

103
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:02,600
Yes.

104
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:07,160
Then I'll go wash my face

105
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:09,800
- so I can come down and cook for you.
- No need.

106
00:09:10,520 --> 00:09:12,680
I'll get some medicine for you.

107
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:25,520
Thank you.

108
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:40,360
Good thing you avoided telling Ms. Kluay
about the documents they tried to take.

109
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:42,240
I almost slipped too.

110
00:09:42,920 --> 00:09:45,640
I remember you insisted
we mustn't tell Kluay

111
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:49,000
that you, Mama Toi, and Som
were planning to investigate her past.

112
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:51,760
Why does someone know our movements?

113
00:09:52,760 --> 00:09:54,600
Could there be someone

114
00:09:54,680 --> 00:09:58,760
who wants information about Kluay
just as much as we do?

115
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:00,680
I find it strange

116
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:03,680
that Mr. Sarut and his wife

117
00:10:03,760 --> 00:10:06,160
made a birthday merit
at Baan Saeng. Don't you think?

118
00:10:09,240 --> 00:10:11,160
The other day, a woman named Nong

119
00:10:11,240 --> 00:10:14,000
called asking for the children's list
at Baan Saeng.

120
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:18,440
What's Mr. Sarut's wife's name again?

121
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:20,440
Anong.

122
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:22,400
If it's the same Anong,

123
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:24,600
that's very strange.

124
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:27,960
How does everything connect?

125
00:10:28,560 --> 00:10:30,640
I don't think
this is a small matter anymore

126
00:10:31,160 --> 00:10:33,160
if it's gotten to the point of bloodshed.

127
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:37,240
I'm worried about Kluay's safety.

128
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:41,600
Then we need to hurry
and find out who's behind that thief.

129
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:47,280
Here you go.

130
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:50,720
From Somwan Delivery Service.

131
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:54,000
And she insists
you video call her while eating.

132
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:55,560
Do I have to finish all this?

133
00:10:55,640 --> 00:10:56,480
Yes.

134
00:10:56,560 --> 00:10:57,760
There's also the Chairwoman's food.

135
00:10:58,480 --> 00:11:00,560
If I finish all of this,

136
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:04,480
I might develop an overeating disorder.

137
00:11:04,560 --> 00:11:07,680
An overeating disorder?

138
00:11:08,280 --> 00:11:09,800
Ugh. The smell of love.

139
00:11:10,880 --> 00:11:11,720
Let's go.

140
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:14,240
So he can be sweet with his Somwan.

141
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:16,880
Mr. Warat, what are you saying?

142
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:18,320
Her sister is right here.

143
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:20,920
I think you two should head back.

144
00:11:21,520 --> 00:11:22,800
You too.

145
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:27,560
Don't worry about anything. Just sleep.

146
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:29,800
Sleep well.

147
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:31,560
You don't even have to wake up.

148
00:11:32,080 --> 00:11:34,680
There are officers guarding the room.

149
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:36,640
I feel like

150
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:38,880
I'm some kind of VIP or something.

151
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:43,200
You two can still joke around.

152
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:46,040
Why does it make me feel uneasy?

153
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:48,080
Don't overthink it.

154
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:50,880
- Let's go. I'm heading back.
- Alright.

155
00:11:51,560 --> 00:11:53,880
But I haven't eaten anything yet.

156
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:55,040
Hey.

157
00:11:55,880 --> 00:11:56,800
Come on.

158
00:11:57,520 --> 00:11:59,920
But I'm hungry.

159
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,680
There's a donut in the car.

160
00:12:01,760 --> 00:12:03,160
- I'll give it to you.
- That's not filling.

161
00:12:23,040 --> 00:12:25,160
Dad. Mom.

162
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:45,680
Dad. Mom.

163
00:12:49,680 --> 00:12:50,520
Dad.

164
00:12:52,760 --> 00:12:53,600
Dad.

165
00:12:57,840 --> 00:12:58,920
Mom.

166
00:13:04,640 --> 00:13:06,040
Dad, what's wrong?

167
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:08,680
Dad. Dad. What happened?!

168
00:13:08,760 --> 00:13:11,640
Mom. Mom. Mom.

169
00:13:12,680 --> 00:13:14,320
Dad. Mom.

170
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:17,240
Mom, get up. Mom.

171
00:13:20,160 --> 00:13:21,800
Mom. Dad.

172
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:24,960
Dad. Mom.

173
00:13:25,040 --> 00:13:26,240
Mom.

174
00:13:31,640 --> 00:13:32,560
Who is he?

175
00:13:33,160 --> 00:13:35,760
Dad, it's me. Sin. Jirasin, your son.

176
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:37,840
It's me, Sin.

177
00:13:40,640 --> 00:13:42,200
You?

178
00:13:42,280 --> 00:13:44,920
You think you're Mr. Jinchai's son?

179
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:52,800
Dad.

180
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:31,280
Dad. Mom.

181
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:35,160
Sin.

182
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:41,160
Mom and I are here to visit you.

183
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:43,960
No. That's not real.

184
00:14:44,040 --> 00:14:45,520
No.

185
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:46,880
Sin.

186
00:14:46,960 --> 00:14:48,600
- Sin.
- Sin.

187
00:14:48,680 --> 00:14:49,480
Sin.

188
00:14:49,560 --> 00:14:51,760
- No. Dad's already dead.
- Sin.

189
00:14:53,040 --> 00:14:55,320
- Sin.
- Go away. Go.

190
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:57,440
- Sin.
- Sin.

191
00:14:58,080 --> 00:15:01,080
Sin. Sin, what's wrong?

192
00:15:02,560 --> 00:15:04,720
I'm right here, Sin.

193
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:08,000
I chased Mom and Dad away.

194
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:12,160
It was just a dream.

195
00:15:12,960 --> 00:15:14,640
I dreamed about Praewilai.

196
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:18,480
What?

197
00:15:19,880 --> 00:15:21,160
What did she do?

198
00:15:22,720 --> 00:15:23,960
Tell me.

199
00:15:24,760 --> 00:15:29,240
Why are you dreaming
about that filthy woman?

200
00:15:30,720 --> 00:15:32,040
It's good I dreamed of her.

201
00:15:33,160 --> 00:15:35,840
So I won't forget
what she did to our family.

202
00:15:38,040 --> 00:15:39,440
Aunt Nong.

203
00:15:39,520 --> 00:15:41,440
Please endure a little longer.

204
00:15:42,760 --> 00:15:45,080
We won't have to live like this anymore.

205
00:15:45,840 --> 00:15:49,040
I'll make every single one of them

206
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:51,120
live under our feet.

207
00:15:52,560 --> 00:15:54,800
Just do as I say.

208
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:57,080
That's enough.

209
00:15:58,240 --> 00:16:01,400
I'll handle the rest.

210
00:16:02,720 --> 00:16:04,680
My hands are already dirty.

211
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:07,680
A little more won't matter.

212
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:09,720
No, Aunt Nong.

213
00:16:10,640 --> 00:16:12,680
You deserve to rest the most.

214
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:16,400
Let me take care of you.

215
00:16:18,600 --> 00:16:21,120
- I'm leaving the hospital tomorrow.
- Sin. Sin.

216
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:22,440
- Why would you do that?
- Ouch!

217
00:16:27,760 --> 00:16:29,120
This accident taught me something.

218
00:16:30,280 --> 00:16:32,160
I don't know how much time I have left.

219
00:16:33,120 --> 00:16:34,480
I can't move slowly anymore.

220
00:16:36,880 --> 00:16:37,920
Warat.

221
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:40,520
You damn mutt.

222
00:16:49,280 --> 00:16:52,480
Grandma isn't home. It feels quiet.

223
00:16:52,560 --> 00:16:53,560
Doesn't feel different at all.

224
00:16:53,640 --> 00:16:54,960
Of course.

225
00:16:55,040 --> 00:16:57,760
You and Grandma
barely talk more than three words.

226
00:16:59,520 --> 00:17:00,640
Shouldn't have given you
the chance to roast me.

227
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:04,400
Mr. Warat, maybe you should call Grandma.

228
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:07,240
She must be worried about the company

229
00:17:07,319 --> 00:17:11,160
with both Sin and Mr. Arnon hospitalized.

230
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:14,960
You just said I barely talk to her.

231
00:17:15,040 --> 00:17:17,560
And now you want me
to make an overseas call?

232
00:17:18,920 --> 00:17:21,920
That's funny. Keep dreaming.

233
00:17:26,359 --> 00:17:28,000
- By the way.
- Hm?

234
00:17:29,880 --> 00:17:31,560
It's actually good Grandma isn't here.

235
00:17:32,160 --> 00:17:34,880
- Why?
- Perfect timing.

236
00:17:35,480 --> 00:17:36,360
For what?

237
00:17:36,440 --> 00:17:37,840
The bedroom,

238
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:40,920
the office, now's the chance.

239
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:42,200
Chance for what?

240
00:17:45,080 --> 00:17:47,800
You mean

241
00:17:48,640 --> 00:17:50,120
to search her room?

242
00:17:50,720 --> 00:17:52,440
No way. Count me out.

243
00:17:52,520 --> 00:17:56,240
Last time we searched the office,

244
00:17:56,320 --> 00:17:57,880
I almost lost my mind.

245
00:17:57,960 --> 00:18:00,480
You know Grandma was serious.

246
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:02,920
What was your initial thought
when I said that?

247
00:18:04,800 --> 00:18:09,720
That we'd search her room.

248
00:18:11,560 --> 00:18:14,440
Fine. If you're scared,
go to bed. Good night.

249
00:18:14,520 --> 00:18:16,200
Hey, Mr. Warat.

250
00:18:16,280 --> 00:18:18,400
Don't. Trust me.

251
00:18:22,120 --> 00:18:24,800
What? Is there something on my face?

252
00:18:27,040 --> 00:18:28,280
Mr. Warat.

253
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:31,240
Why are you looking at me like that?

254
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:33,800
Okay, Kluay.

255
00:18:34,960 --> 00:18:37,120
I won't search Grandma's room.

256
00:18:42,920 --> 00:18:44,600
You…

257
00:18:45,520 --> 00:18:46,840
Did you see something?

258
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,240
Can you see signs like I can?

259
00:18:50,400 --> 00:18:53,160
Not exactly. But I…

260
00:18:54,560 --> 00:18:55,440
I saw you…

261
00:19:00,080 --> 00:19:01,440
Anyway,

262
00:19:02,760 --> 00:19:04,600
we're not searching.

263
00:19:04,680 --> 00:19:06,040
- Mm.
- Let's go to bed.

264
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:09,080
Sleep in my room.

265
00:19:10,240 --> 00:19:11,880
You want me to sleep in your room?

266
00:19:12,520 --> 00:19:14,680
- Why?
- What are you thinking?

267
00:19:18,840 --> 00:19:22,440
I'm not thinking anything. But trust me.

268
00:19:23,400 --> 00:19:24,880
Go sleep in my room. Go.

269
00:19:24,960 --> 00:19:26,440
Wait, Mr. Warat.

270
00:19:26,520 --> 00:19:28,840
Let's talk first. Don't drag me like this.

271
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:31,560
You can use my bathroom.

272
00:19:32,160 --> 00:19:34,920
I can't even go get my things?

273
00:19:35,560 --> 00:19:38,680
No. I'm too lazy to stand guard.

274
00:19:39,800 --> 00:19:42,880
Just wear my clothes. They're clean.

275
00:19:43,480 --> 00:19:46,600
I'm not saying your things are dirty.

276
00:19:46,680 --> 00:19:48,920
I just want to know what you saw.

277
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:52,080
Nothing.

278
00:19:52,840 --> 00:19:56,160
I get it now how uncomfortable it feels
when you warn someone about a sign.

279
00:19:56,840 --> 00:19:59,480
Then tell me what you saw.

280
00:20:01,120 --> 00:20:02,200
You…

281
00:20:03,120 --> 00:20:03,960
What about me?

282
00:20:06,280 --> 00:20:07,320
Nothing.

283
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:10,640
Go shower and change.
I'll stay awake and watch over you.

284
00:20:12,240 --> 00:20:15,040
Let's see if I can protect you

285
00:20:15,680 --> 00:20:16,960
even in my own house.

286
00:20:29,600 --> 00:20:30,680
Kluay.

287
00:20:31,760 --> 00:20:32,600
Are you asleep?

288
00:20:35,120 --> 00:20:38,840
If you keep asking me that,
neither of us will sleep.

289
00:20:40,080 --> 00:20:41,680
I want to know…

290
00:20:43,040 --> 00:20:44,640
how certain this sign is.

291
00:20:45,920 --> 00:20:48,440
From my experience,

292
00:20:48,520 --> 00:20:50,720
it's 99%.

293
00:20:52,520 --> 00:20:55,800
Then… I won't sleep.

294
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:36,360
Kluay.

295
00:21:38,560 --> 00:21:39,400
Kluay.

296
00:21:43,240 --> 00:21:46,400
Kluay. Kluay.

297
00:21:52,440 --> 00:21:53,560
Kluay.

298
00:21:55,240 --> 00:21:56,880
Are you downstairs?

299
00:21:59,840 --> 00:22:01,000
Answer me.

300
00:22:02,040 --> 00:22:04,000
Don't tease me.

301
00:22:04,080 --> 00:22:05,040
Kluay.

302
00:22:05,120 --> 00:22:06,280
I'm here.

303
00:22:09,840 --> 00:22:10,840
In the kitchen?

304
00:22:13,560 --> 00:22:17,120
Yes. I was hungry,
so I came down to find something to eat.

305
00:22:17,720 --> 00:22:20,720
I even came down quietly by myself,
and you still followed me.

306
00:22:20,800 --> 00:22:22,120
Go. Go upstairs and sleep.

307
00:22:23,080 --> 00:22:24,560
No.

308
00:22:24,640 --> 00:22:26,480
I'll wait until you finish eating,
then we'll go up together.

309
00:22:28,120 --> 00:22:29,720
Suit yourself.

310
00:22:33,400 --> 00:22:34,280
Want some?

311
00:22:46,160 --> 00:22:48,120
Don't you feel something familiar?

312
00:22:51,040 --> 00:22:51,880
Familiar how?

313
00:22:53,080 --> 00:22:55,640
Like in our past life,
we already kissed before.

314
00:23:17,280 --> 00:23:18,440
<i>Don't you feel it?</i>

315
00:23:24,560 --> 00:23:25,920
My sign was accurate after all.

316
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:31,560
At least, in the image I saw,

317
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:34,560
you looked just like this.

318
00:23:37,480 --> 00:23:40,640
You mean… with tomato sauce on my face?

319
00:23:42,120 --> 00:23:45,680
Where's the danger in your sign?

320
00:23:46,280 --> 00:23:48,000
It doesn't have to be dangerous.

321
00:23:48,080 --> 00:23:49,480
It could be something good.

322
00:23:50,080 --> 00:23:52,760
Are you arguing
with someone experienced like me?

323
00:23:53,600 --> 00:23:54,840
You really think you're experienced?

324
00:23:57,280 --> 00:23:59,520
I've seen signs since I was a kid.

325
00:23:59,600 --> 00:24:02,080
I've seen them my whole life.
I would know…

326
00:24:02,160 --> 00:24:04,240
I didn't mean about the signs.

327
00:24:08,240 --> 00:24:09,560
Go to bed.

328
00:24:10,320 --> 00:24:11,640
Fine. I'll go.

329
00:24:22,080 --> 00:24:25,400
Kluay… what were you thinking?

330
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:37,800
You know I'm worried,
and you make me worry even more, Kluay.

331
00:24:42,640 --> 00:24:43,960
What are you muttering about?

332
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:53,040
About you.

333
00:24:53,120 --> 00:24:56,080
Where did you go?
I told you to stay close to me.

334
00:24:56,680 --> 00:24:58,520
- Are you worried about me?
- No.

335
00:25:00,720 --> 00:25:02,880
Didn't you say
you didn't believe in signs anymore?

336
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:07,560
You're the one who said
a sign can only mean something bad.

337
00:25:08,480 --> 00:25:10,440
So that means you admit

338
00:25:10,520 --> 00:25:14,600
your tomato sauce sign wasn't real?

339
00:25:15,360 --> 00:25:18,040
- I wish it were real.
- Why?

340
00:25:18,120 --> 00:25:20,480
So you'd be safe.

341
00:25:22,840 --> 00:25:24,360
Thank you.

342
00:25:25,240 --> 00:25:26,360
Thank you for what?

343
00:25:28,360 --> 00:25:29,280
Who's calling?

344
00:25:32,520 --> 00:25:33,640
Hello, Mom?

345
00:25:35,560 --> 00:25:39,040
A volunteer fainted?
Is she seriously hurt?

346
00:25:42,240 --> 00:25:43,800
<i>Is she badly injured?</i>

347
00:25:44,600 --> 00:25:49,000
<i>Is she badly injured?</i>

348
00:25:49,080 --> 00:25:53,640
<i>Is she badly injured?</i>

349
00:25:53,720 --> 00:25:56,320
<i>Is she badly injured?</i>

350
00:25:56,400 --> 00:25:59,320
<i>Is she badly injured?</i>

351
00:26:00,040 --> 00:26:03,360
<i>Is she badly injured?</i>

352
00:26:03,440 --> 00:26:07,440
<i>Is she badly injured?</i>

353
00:26:08,080 --> 00:26:12,600
<i>Is she badly injured?</i>

354
00:26:13,320 --> 00:26:15,000
<i>Is she badly injured?</i>

355
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:18,160
Please stay with your grandma
over there, Master.

356
00:26:18,240 --> 00:26:20,520
<i>Is she badly injured?</i>

357
00:26:21,800 --> 00:26:23,680
Is she badly injured?

358
00:26:26,440 --> 00:26:27,520
Hey, Kluay.

359
00:26:29,280 --> 00:26:30,440
I remember now.

360
00:26:31,920 --> 00:26:34,480
- The person who said that sentence.
- What sentence?

361
00:26:35,160 --> 00:26:38,360
The, "Is she seriously hurt?"

362
00:26:39,120 --> 00:26:42,480
She said it when my mom
fell from the building.

363
00:26:43,560 --> 00:26:44,720
Who said it?

364
00:26:44,800 --> 00:26:46,960
Is she badly injured?

365
00:26:49,600 --> 00:26:51,840
Ms. Anong. Jirasin's aunt.

366
00:26:53,480 --> 00:26:54,880
What?

367
00:27:02,680 --> 00:27:05,000
If Ms. Anong was there

368
00:27:07,280 --> 00:27:08,840
when your mother died,

369
00:27:09,400 --> 00:27:13,800
then is it possible
she was very familiar with Vanich Mall?

370
00:27:14,840 --> 00:27:16,280
It's possible.

371
00:27:17,200 --> 00:27:20,640
That area is behind the office building.

372
00:27:22,560 --> 00:27:24,240
It's not part of the mall itself.

373
00:27:24,960 --> 00:27:28,560
Only employees or related personnel

374
00:27:29,160 --> 00:27:31,480
could access that zone.

375
00:27:33,280 --> 00:27:34,600
Do you remember

376
00:27:34,680 --> 00:27:37,280
what Ameena's housekeeper said?

377
00:27:37,360 --> 00:27:40,400
That Pong used to work
at Mr. Sarut's logistics company?

378
00:27:42,800 --> 00:27:44,920
And Mr. Arnon also said

379
00:27:45,680 --> 00:27:49,160
that company used to be
a business partner of Vanich Mall.

380
00:27:50,160 --> 00:27:51,880
Then is it possible

381
00:27:51,960 --> 00:27:53,600
Ms. Anong went there

382
00:27:53,680 --> 00:27:56,640
on business related
to Mr. Sarut's logistics company

383
00:27:57,240 --> 00:28:01,160
and happened to witness
what happened to your mother?

384
00:28:01,800 --> 00:28:03,320
Or maybe Ms. Anong

385
00:28:04,360 --> 00:28:08,480
is the one who can answer
what really happened to my mother.

386
00:28:11,240 --> 00:28:13,160
I think so too.

387
00:28:13,240 --> 00:28:15,280
At the very least, she could tell you

388
00:28:16,280 --> 00:28:19,240
what your mother was like
at the moment she died.

389
00:28:21,440 --> 00:28:23,320
It can't just be that.

390
00:28:23,400 --> 00:28:25,360
If she was at the scene

391
00:28:26,240 --> 00:28:29,440
and still asked people around,
"Is she badly injured?"

392
00:28:30,480 --> 00:28:32,560
then she must know more than that.

393
00:28:37,720 --> 00:28:38,840
You're right.

394
00:28:38,920 --> 00:28:40,560
So how do we…

395
00:28:41,920 --> 00:28:45,680
get close to her? We can't just
show up at that house out of nowhere.

396
00:28:46,800 --> 00:28:50,320
Jirasin and I can barely see each other
without wanting to kill each other.

397
00:28:50,400 --> 00:28:53,240
And I don't think you can handle it.

398
00:28:53,320 --> 00:28:55,160
Last time, you almost didn't make it out.

399
00:28:55,800 --> 00:28:57,200
Don't worry about me.

400
00:28:57,280 --> 00:29:00,440
It's already come this far.
I can handle it. I'll go.

401
00:29:01,800 --> 00:29:03,000
Are you sure?

402
00:29:04,160 --> 00:29:05,280
Yes.

403
00:29:05,360 --> 00:29:07,200
At least I'll have you with me.

404
00:29:07,280 --> 00:29:10,080
If something happens,
you can just take me out.

405
00:29:10,160 --> 00:29:12,320
You trust me that much?

406
00:29:12,400 --> 00:29:14,200
Aren't you afraid I'll run
and save myself?

407
00:29:14,280 --> 00:29:17,400
If you can bring yourself
to do that, try it.

408
00:29:18,520 --> 00:29:19,920
This won't be easy.

409
00:29:21,160 --> 00:29:22,800
We need Ms. Anong to talk.

410
00:29:24,040 --> 00:29:28,480
About my mother. And about Pong and Soi.

411
00:29:29,840 --> 00:29:32,240
If it's about Pong and Soi,

412
00:29:32,320 --> 00:29:35,320
wouldn't it be easier
to go straight to Mr. Sarut?

413
00:29:35,920 --> 00:29:37,000
That's true.

414
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:40,400
He was their boss.

415
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:44,920
But are you sure
those two are really dead?

416
00:29:48,520 --> 00:29:53,080
If they appeared in a sign like that,
I don't think they survived.

417
00:29:56,520 --> 00:29:57,720
What?

418
00:29:58,840 --> 00:30:00,080
Yes?

419
00:30:06,800 --> 00:30:07,480
WELCOME TO BAAN SAENG WAN MAI

420
00:30:07,560 --> 00:30:10,000
Don't say anything, dear.

421
00:30:10,080 --> 00:30:11,520
Won't she get suspicious

422
00:30:11,600 --> 00:30:13,280
if we never let her come home?

423
00:30:14,040 --> 00:30:17,880
Let her be suspicious. It's better than
letting her be in danger.

424
00:30:18,400 --> 00:30:20,520
From now on, any outsider who comes in

425
00:30:20,600 --> 00:30:24,200
has to register and leave
their information. If anything happens,

426
00:30:24,280 --> 00:30:26,520
we'll have records to investigate.

427
00:30:27,200 --> 00:30:28,400
Not like this time

428
00:30:28,480 --> 00:30:31,040
when we couldn't trace anyone.

429
00:30:31,640 --> 00:30:33,560
Right now, Arnon and Mr. Warat

430
00:30:33,640 --> 00:30:35,080
are thinking along the same lines

431
00:30:35,160 --> 00:30:38,680
that the documents the thief took
are related to Kluay.

432
00:30:39,320 --> 00:30:41,360
And the person Arnon suspects

433
00:30:41,440 --> 00:30:43,360
is Ms. Anong.

434
00:30:44,480 --> 00:30:46,160
It makes sense to suspect her.

435
00:30:46,240 --> 00:30:50,720
The timing was too coincidental.

436
00:30:51,320 --> 00:30:55,000
And there's also the issue
of someone checking the children's list.

437
00:30:55,080 --> 00:30:58,800
She even lied to me,
saying that she didn't know Kluay.

438
00:30:59,400 --> 00:31:00,480
That's true.

439
00:31:02,360 --> 00:31:05,560
I should have listened to your warning.

440
00:31:06,240 --> 00:31:08,920
If I'd known it would escalate like this,

441
00:31:09,600 --> 00:31:12,360
I wouldn't have dug into Kluay's past.

442
00:31:13,720 --> 00:31:15,480
You did the right thing.

443
00:31:15,560 --> 00:31:17,120
Otherwise, would we have known

444
00:31:17,200 --> 00:31:19,840
that someone dangerous was watching her?

445
00:31:27,720 --> 00:31:30,040
She's just one small girl.

446
00:31:30,680 --> 00:31:32,920
What do they want from her?

447
00:31:35,080 --> 00:31:37,200
If we know who Kluay really is,

448
00:31:37,280 --> 00:31:38,880
then we'll know who they are too.

449
00:31:39,600 --> 00:31:42,280
Maybe Ms. Anong

450
00:31:42,360 --> 00:31:44,520
has nothing to do with her at all.

451
00:31:44,600 --> 00:31:46,040
Anything is possible.

452
00:31:47,760 --> 00:31:50,600
Then we have to hurry.

453
00:31:52,800 --> 00:31:53,880
Kluay…

454
00:32:08,760 --> 00:32:11,080
Stay still.

455
00:32:11,160 --> 00:32:13,040
Just a little longer.
Just a little, I promise.

456
00:32:13,120 --> 00:32:15,600
I've been staying still
for an hour already.

457
00:32:16,440 --> 00:32:17,760
I can't take it. I'm sore.

458
00:32:18,360 --> 00:32:19,800
That's because you keep complaining

459
00:32:19,880 --> 00:32:22,600
and moving like that.
That's why Ms. Ampha disappeared.

460
00:32:23,480 --> 00:32:25,360
- Shh.
- Look, if Ms. Ampha

461
00:32:25,440 --> 00:32:27,160
covered my mouth,
that means she doesn't want me to talk.

462
00:32:27,240 --> 00:32:29,880
So I'll just not talk.
That's it. It's not hard.

463
00:32:30,720 --> 00:32:32,400
But that's not all I want to know.

464
00:32:32,480 --> 00:32:35,360
Aren't you curious? Ms. Ampha's
been gone for so long. How has she been?

465
00:32:35,440 --> 00:32:37,520
She might need our help.

466
00:32:39,160 --> 00:32:42,120
So you want me to stay still
so she'll show up? That makes no sense.

467
00:32:42,200 --> 00:32:44,280
Are you crazy? No. I'm not doing this.

468
00:32:45,200 --> 00:32:46,640
Stop. Stay still.

469
00:32:46,720 --> 00:32:49,160
- Kluay, I can't take it. I need to pee.
- You… What?

470
00:32:49,240 --> 00:32:51,640
- Just a little longer.
- I can't.

471
00:32:51,720 --> 00:32:54,280
Stay still. Shh. No complaining.

472
00:33:05,640 --> 00:33:08,160
Do you want to know what I said?

473
00:33:09,120 --> 00:33:11,120
Yeah. What did you say?

474
00:33:11,200 --> 00:33:13,400
Why didn't I hear
anything you said at all?

475
00:33:13,480 --> 00:33:16,600
I just said
we have to go to Mr. Sarut's house.

476
00:33:17,760 --> 00:33:19,920
Ms. Ampha.

477
00:33:20,000 --> 00:33:22,160
How is it? Did she say

478
00:33:23,320 --> 00:33:24,680
why she won't let us go?

479
00:33:25,320 --> 00:33:27,960
Ms. Ampha, please don't be mad at us.

480
00:33:28,040 --> 00:33:29,840
Mr. Warat is just curious, that's all.

481
00:33:29,920 --> 00:33:31,400
We're not being stubborn.

482
00:33:32,320 --> 00:33:33,640
Anyway,

483
00:33:34,240 --> 00:33:36,800
how have you been?
You've been gone so long.

484
00:33:36,880 --> 00:33:38,320
I've been worried.

485
00:33:39,560 --> 00:33:40,640
Did she answer?

486
00:33:41,800 --> 00:33:43,080
- Uh.
- Did she?

487
00:33:43,160 --> 00:33:44,480
No answer.

488
00:33:46,320 --> 00:33:47,880
Yeah, Ms. Ampha.

489
00:33:47,960 --> 00:33:50,960
If something's wrong, can you tell me?

490
00:33:51,040 --> 00:33:53,800
I don't understand
why you won't let us go.

491
00:33:56,080 --> 00:33:57,520
- Did she answer?
- No.

492
00:33:58,160 --> 00:34:00,200
- Playing hard to get.
- Hey, Mr. Warat.

493
00:34:00,840 --> 00:34:01,800
Okay.

494
00:34:03,200 --> 00:34:04,720
Then let's just go.

495
00:34:07,560 --> 00:34:09,000
- Mr. Warat.
- Ouch.

496
00:34:09,920 --> 00:34:11,360
Why are you so clumsy?

497
00:34:12,360 --> 00:34:13,760
Geez, Ms. Ampha.

498
00:34:14,400 --> 00:34:15,800
Thought you didn't have
that much strength.

499
00:34:15,880 --> 00:34:17,480
Ms. Ampha?

500
00:34:31,880 --> 00:34:34,040
Since we're passing by anyway,

501
00:34:34,120 --> 00:34:36,440
let's stop by the hospital,

502
00:34:36,520 --> 00:34:38,800
so we can visit Jirasin and Arnon too.

503
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:41,400
With the utmost respect, ma'am.

504
00:34:41,480 --> 00:34:44,080
You've just landed and must be tired.
Won't you rest first?

505
00:34:44,159 --> 00:34:45,639
No.

506
00:34:45,719 --> 00:34:48,120
If I rest, it'll just keep eating at me.

507
00:34:49,360 --> 00:34:50,639
Even if I go home now,

508
00:34:50,719 --> 00:34:53,960
I guarantee that within an hour,
I'll end up calling you

509
00:34:54,040 --> 00:34:56,239
to pick me up and take me
to visit those two anyway.

510
00:34:57,200 --> 00:35:01,000
And about Mr. Jirasin,
are you going to speak to him today?

511
00:35:01,080 --> 00:35:02,280
Not yet.

512
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:06,000
And it has nothing to do
with him being sick.

513
00:35:06,080 --> 00:35:07,640
Yes, ma'am.

514
00:35:07,720 --> 00:35:10,120
We're only missing
Mr. Chatchai's explanation.

515
00:35:12,320 --> 00:35:14,080
But honestly,

516
00:35:14,920 --> 00:35:17,760
I actually like it

517
00:35:17,840 --> 00:35:20,280
when those two go at each other like this.

518
00:35:39,480 --> 00:35:40,520
Anong.

519
00:35:41,240 --> 00:35:43,360
What on earth happened to you?

520
00:35:45,400 --> 00:35:49,560
CAPTAIN CHADA

521
00:35:51,560 --> 00:35:52,800
Yes, hello, Captain.

522
00:35:52,880 --> 00:35:55,000
<i>Yes, it's me, Rut.</i>

523
00:35:55,080 --> 00:35:57,640
<i>I've been calling since yesterday.</i>
<i>You didn't pick up.</i>

524
00:35:57,720 --> 00:36:01,240
Oh, yes. Sorry,
yesterday I had errands all day.

525
00:36:01,320 --> 00:36:02,480
Do you need anything?

526
00:36:02,560 --> 00:36:04,440
<i>Yesterday I ran into Anong.</i>

527
00:36:05,200 --> 00:36:07,840
Anong? Where?

528
00:36:07,920 --> 00:36:09,400
<i>Right at the alley by your house.</i>

529
00:36:09,480 --> 00:36:12,120
<i>But what shocked me was</i>

530
00:36:12,200 --> 00:36:14,000
<i>she looked like she'd been</i>
<i>in a fight with someone.</i>

531
00:36:28,240 --> 00:36:30,000
I never thought I'd run into you here.

532
00:36:31,000 --> 00:36:32,960
I'm not surprised

533
00:36:33,040 --> 00:36:34,040
to see you here either.

534
00:36:35,160 --> 00:36:38,240
Don't tell me you already knew
I got into an accident.

535
00:36:40,840 --> 00:36:43,000
Oh right, that day,
Mr. Warat came to visit me in my room.

536
00:36:44,520 --> 00:36:46,680
Mr. Warat came to visit you?

537
00:36:47,440 --> 00:36:49,080
I don't think Mr. Warat

538
00:36:49,160 --> 00:36:52,360
should be visiting or getting
that friendly with his enemy.

539
00:36:54,560 --> 00:36:57,360
So you're trying to say I'm corrupt?

540
00:36:58,880 --> 00:36:59,960
No.

541
00:37:00,040 --> 00:37:01,760
I was just stating the facts.

542
00:37:02,480 --> 00:37:05,440
I saw what I saw, so I said it.

543
00:37:05,520 --> 00:37:07,800
You've incomplete information,

544
00:37:07,880 --> 00:37:10,120
and you go around announcing I'm corrupt.

545
00:37:11,720 --> 00:37:13,400
You shouldn't say things like that.

546
00:37:14,240 --> 00:37:16,400
You got stabbed
and can't trace who did it at all.

547
00:37:17,880 --> 00:37:20,040
Oh, good that you brought that up.

548
00:37:20,880 --> 00:37:25,040
Because I'm starting to suspect
it was someone inside Vanich

549
00:37:25,120 --> 00:37:26,800
who sent someone to stab me.

550
00:37:28,240 --> 00:37:31,720
If you say that,
I can sue you for defamation.

551
00:37:31,800 --> 00:37:33,360
Go ahead.

552
00:37:33,440 --> 00:37:35,360
Then I'll dig up other things too.

553
00:37:36,160 --> 00:37:37,880
I didn't hire anyone to stab you.

554
00:37:37,960 --> 00:37:41,000
If I were going to do it,
I'd do it myself right to your face.

555
00:37:41,080 --> 00:37:42,280
How about right now?

556
00:37:46,800 --> 00:37:49,520
<i>I think it's getting more dangerous.</i>

557
00:37:50,040 --> 00:37:51,840
<i>What if the real target</i>

558
00:37:51,920 --> 00:37:54,760
isn't Mr. Arnon, but the two of us?

559
00:37:54,840 --> 00:37:56,040
NEXT EPISODE

560
00:37:56,120 --> 00:37:57,880
<i>If there's anything you can forgive,</i>

561
00:37:57,960 --> 00:38:00,080
you should forgive him.

562
00:38:00,160 --> 00:38:03,400
You're talking like he's going to die.

563
00:38:03,480 --> 00:38:06,240
<i>I think Ms. Ampha has warned us</i>
<i>many times already</i>

564
00:38:06,320 --> 00:38:08,120
<i>whenever</i>
<i>we're about to go to Mr. Sarut's house.</i>

565
00:38:08,200 --> 00:38:10,920
I've had a bad feeling about it too.

566
00:38:11,480 --> 00:38:13,000
<i>If there are so many problems,</i>

567
00:38:13,080 --> 00:38:15,440
<i>he should just die. So, it'll be over.</i>

568
00:38:17,560 --> 00:38:18,640
That's Mr. Arnon.

569
00:38:19,480 --> 00:38:20,920
Where?

570
00:40:48,960 --> 00:40:50,760
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
